# shadcn/ui Standards

## Setup
- Style: base-nova
- Icon library: lucide-react
- Component location: components/ui/
- Config: components.json

## Usage Rules
- Always import from '@/components/ui/[component]'
- Never modify files inside components/ui/ directly
- Use shadcn CLI to add new components:
  npx shadcn@latest add [component]
- Customize via className prop, not by editing source

## Button Usage
```tsx
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'

// Primary — lime green
<Button
  className="bg-[#CCFF00] text-black hover:opacity-90 rounded-full px-8 py-4"
  size="lg"
>
  VIEW WORK
</Button>

// Secondary — outline
<Button
  variant="outline"
  className="rounded-full px-8 py-4 border-[var(--text-primary)]"
  size="lg"
>
  GET IN TOUCH
</Button>
```

## Available Components (add as needed)
Run: npx shadcn@latest add [name]
- button ← already used
- card ← for project cards
- badge ← for skill tags
- separator ← for dividers
- dialog ← for modals
- form ← for contact form
- input ← for contact form
- textarea ← for contact form
- toast ← for form submission feedback

## Token Conflicts
shadcn owns: --border, --accent, --background, --foreground
We own: --custom-border, --lime, --bg-primary, --text-primary
Never override shadcn tokens with our values.